  "description" : "JLVM ZK / auth-DB opcode cross-language test vectors. Scala (metakit) is the reference; Rust (jlvm-core) must reproduce every expected value byte-for-byte. Same structure and differential-runner contract as json_logic_test_vectors.json. The 'known_answer' category carries independent ground truth (circomlib poseidon, real SP1 groth16 fixture, RFC-9381 ECVRF-EDWARDS25519, EIP-197 pairing identity). bls_verify / bls_aggregate_verify are DEFERRED to Tier 3 (switching from MIRACL-SVDW to the eth2 SSWU ciphersuite). ERROR CONVENTION: a case with \"error\": true (and NO \"expected\") asserts that evaluation MUST FAIL in every implementation (the Scala reference raises a JsonLogicException or throws); all other cases carry \"expected\" and must reproduce it byte-for-byte.",
